  "prompt": "Does computer kill brain cells?",
  "response": "There is no scientific evidence to suggest that using a computer kills brain cells. However, excessive screen time and poor posture associated with prolonged computer use can lead to various health issues, such as eye strain, headaches, and musculoskeletal problems. It's important to take regular breaks, practice good ergonomics, and balance screen time with other activities to maintain overall well-being. Engaging in a variety of mental and physical activities can help keep your brain healthy.",
